      "finance": "There's a good chance you'll get money back from someone who borrowed from you long ago — not necessarily the most recent borrower. They may reach out to catch up and return the money with an apology. Better late than never. If you're having financial difficulties, you can turn to close friends or family for help. Those you've shown kindness to in the past are ready to return the favor. If you need to cut expenses, you might consider moving back in with family.",
